<div class="one-time-password-help-guide">
  <h2>What is Two Factor Authentication?</h2>

  <p>
    <%= _("Two factor authentication adds extra security to your account by " \
          "requiring more information to reset your password.") %>
  </p>

  <p>
    <%= _("Only the correct combination of confirming your account through " \
          "an email token and entering the correct one time password will " \
          "allow your account password to be changed.") %>
  </p>

  <p>
    <%= _("You will be given a one time password when you enable two factor " \
          "authentication. Do not share this password. You can either keep " \
          "it in your password manager, or print it and keep it somewhere " \
          "safe.") %>
  </p>

  <p>
    <%= _("When you want to change your account password, you will also need " \
          "to enter your two factor one time password. Your one time " \
          "password can only be used once, so a new one will be generated " \
          "after you've successfully changed your password. You'll need to " \
          "update your password manager or print the new password.") %>
  </p>

  <p>
    <%= _("You can regenerate your one time password at any time.") %>
  </p>
</div>
